## What is ChemPy?

- Python package useful for physical chemistry.
- It uses the scientific python stack (numpy, scipy, matplotlib & scipy).

.left-column[
<img src="python.png" alt="KTH" style="width:100%">
]
.right-column[
<center>
<font style="font-size:200pt">⚗
</center>
]


---

## What can you do with ChemPy?

*Parse chemical formulas from strings:*
```py
>>> from chempy import Substance as S
>>> ferricn = S.from_formula('Fe(CN)6-3')
>>> ferricn.composition
{0: -3, 26: 1, 6: 6, 7: 6}
>>> ferricn.mass
211.955
```

---

## What can you do with ChemPy?

*Parse chemical formulas from strings:*
```py
>>> print(ferricn.unicode_name)
Fe(CN)₆³⁻
>>> print(ferricn.latex_name)
Fe(CN)_{6}^{3-}
>>> print(ferricn.html_name)
Fe(CN)<sub>6</sub><sup>3-</sup>
```

---

## What can you do with ChemPy? <img src="atlantis.jpg" alt="Space shuttle" style="width:30%; float: right">
*Balancing chemical reactions:*
<center>
<span class="qmark">?</span>NH<sub>4</sub>ClO<sub>4</sub> + <span class="qmark">?</span>Al <b>&rarr;</b> <span class="qmark">?</span>Al<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub> + <span class="qmark">?</span>HCl + <span class="qmark">?</span>H<sub>2</sub>O + <span class="qmark">?</span>N<sub>2</sub>
</center>
```py
>>> import chempy
>>> r = {'NH4ClO4', 'Al'}
>>> p = {'Al2O3', 'HCl', 'H2O', 'N2'}
```
---

## What can you do with ChemPy? <img src="atlantis.jpg" alt="Space shuttle" style="width:30%; float: right">
*Balancing chemical reactions:*
<center>
<span class="qmark">?</span>NH<sub>4</sub>ClO<sub>4</sub> + <span class="qmark">?</span>Al <b>&rarr;</b> <span class="qmark">?</span>Al<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub> + <span class="qmark">?</span>HCl + <span class="qmark">?</span>H<sub>2</sub>O + <span class="qmark">?</span>N<sub>2</sub>
</center>
```py
>>> import chempy
>>> r = {'NH4ClO4', 'Al'}
>>> p = {'Al2O3', 'HCl', 'H2O', 'N2'}
>>> a = chempy.balance_stoichiometry(r, p)
>>> print(a[0])
{'Al': 10, 'NH4ClO4': 6}
>>> print(a[1])
{'Al2O3': 5, 'H2O': 9, 'HCl': 6, 'N2': 3}
```
